Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.76,0:00:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome again to follow folk poem's radio show. I Risto Vaasranta will be your host.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.80,0:00:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can all send your poems to the show. I will read them in the night's quiet grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.40,0:00:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And as always, what makes this interesting is that I will be reading them for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.28,0:00:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take the first poem of the night. This one was sent by Matti from Maankorpi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.84,0:00:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, People's dues.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.20,0:01:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Companies reap what they sow. The people want much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.12,0:01:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Does my life have dues? Does my life have a meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.96,0:01:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,From account to account, money, always just money.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.88,0:01:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,From account to another. I eat my money every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.44,0:01:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next poem comes from Veikko in Niuva.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.24,0:01:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, Gentle touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.00,0:01:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at me, what do you see? Will you touch me like I touch you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.04,0:01:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you touch me like I touch you? Will this end? Will this not end? How can I serve better?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.32,0:02:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity's hope, is it my responsibility? Leave me alone. Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.16,0:02:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I miss small and warm in my lap. I miss two small and warm in my lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't put them in a barrel. I will just hold them in my lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next poem is from Reima in Lappeenpohja.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.44,0:02:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, Lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.76,0:02:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If I got a million, I would marry the world, I would get married, if I had time for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.76,0:03:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman will do, whoever woman, I won't choose wrong, I will choose the best for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.80,0:03:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, let me win in the lottery, let me win the lottery of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My life would be worth millions if I could embrace you, Irma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.32,0:03:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you hear me? I cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.80,0:03:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next poem is from Arvi in Pohjanpolska.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, To you, to me, to everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.08,0:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I sit in the spring, in autumn worshiping, your breast, crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:04:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,From my lap I wrap a pretty phrase, a song phrase, a phrase of a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.44,0:04:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ground I sow a potato.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.08,0:04:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,From potato I make soup. From the soup, a tune of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.32,0:04:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My phrase is, sausage soup, a'la carte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next poem is from Teppo in Laitesmaa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, Reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I go a long way, to the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.72,0:04:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There I see life, experience life, how I need you, how you need me, how you need us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Be my reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:05:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Be for me, what jumps afar, be my Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next poem is from Kaapo in Enteisto.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.24,0:05:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, Box of confectionery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.84,0:05:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I close you in my heart, I close you all the time. Who has the last bite?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it fit in your mouth like it does in mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or will it fit in someone else's mouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.44,0:05:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What might be the contents? Will it be sweet or will it be sour?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't understand. Who can resist these? Best taste. Be my confectionery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.20,0:06:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Next poem is from Juhani in Paasjarvi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.76,0:06:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, Life's milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.40,0:06:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope much from life. From the store I get my milk. I feel proud, at the cashier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When we don't have anything to give, anyone else but ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we value whom makes milk for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we value whom makes us drink it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.56,0:06:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we value anyone? Anyone who really needs it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.40,0:06:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us value, be my mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last poem of the night, sent to us by anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Name of the poem, Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.40,0:07:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's bread will you eat, when nights are dark for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Much you speak, do little. Who believes this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.32,0:07:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, again and again. The nights are spoiled again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Has anyone ever needed poems?
